NZ_CP094655.1-56	MetaGeneAnnotator	CDS	23748	24326	.	-	0	ID=MGA_656;product=nitrate reductase molybdenum cofactor assembly chaperone;inference=COORDINATES:ab initio prediction:MetaGeneAnnotator,similar to AA sequence:RefSeq:WP_011101445.1;translation=MINFAKINQLQDVFVALSRLIDYPDQETFSPEMRAALVENPALSKEQQVTFGELFDELNQGTLLDQESHFASLFEMNRRYTLYMSYYKMTDSRERGTILAKLKMMYEMFGVAETTSELADYLPMLLEFFAYGDFMDDSRQDDLQLALGVIEDGTYSLLQNALADADDPYMKLIKAVRGLIRSCVETEANAHA;locus_tag=LOCUS_06510;gene=narJ;note=WP_011101445.1 nitrate reductase molybdenum cofactor assembly chaperone (Lactiplantibacillus) [pid:59.4%25%2C q_cov:96.9%25%2C s_cov:97.4%25%2C Eval:6.8e-58],Domain:cl00958:Nitrate_red_del Nitrate reductase delta subunit. Type II members of the DMSO reductase family are heterotrimeric proteins with bis(molybdopterin guanine dinucleotide)Mo%2C iron-sulfur%2C and heme b prosthetic groups bound by the alpha%2C beta%2C and gamma subunits respectively. Members of this protein family are not part of the mature protein%2C although they are the product of a fourth clustered gene. Proteins in this family are interpreted as a chaperone%2C analogous to NarJ of nitrate reductases. [Superfamily%2C Aligned:8-190%2C Eval:5.5e-29%2C score:103.2],MGA_656
NZ_CP094655.1-56	MetaGeneAnnotator	CDS	24319	25878	.	-	0	ID=MGA_657;product=nitrate reductase subunit beta;inference=COORDINATES:ab initio prediction:MetaGeneAnnotator,similar to AA sequence:RefSeq:WP_011101444.1;;locus_tag=LOCUS_06520;gene=narH;note=WP_011101444.1 nitrate reductase subunit beta (Lactiplantibacillus) [pid:87.9%25%2C q_cov:100.0%25%2C s_cov:100.0%25%2C Eval:2.5e-285],Domain:cl25360:DMSOR_beta-like Beta subunit of the DMSO Reductase (DMSOR) family. This family consists of the small beta iron-sulfur (FeS) subunit of the DMSO Reductase (DMSOR) family. Members of this family also contain a large%2C periplasmic molybdenum-containing alpha subunit and may have a small gamma subunit as well.  Examples of heterodimeric members with alpha and beta subunits include arsenite oxidase%2C and tungsten-containing formate dehydrogenase (FDH-T) while   heterotrimeric members containing alpha%2C beta%2C and gamma subunits include formate dehydrogenase-N (FDH-N)%2C and nitrate reductase (NarGHI).  The beta subunit contains four Fe4/S4 and/or Fe3/S4 clusters which transfer the electrons from the alpha subunit to a hydrophobic integral membrane protein%2C presumably a cytochrome containing two b-type heme groups. The reducing equivalents are then transferred to menaquinone%2C which finally reduces the electron-accepting enzyme system. [Superfamily%2C Aligned:1-519%2C Eval:0.0e+00%2C score:856.7],MGA_657
