NZ_CP094655.1-69	MetaGeneAnnotator	CDS	21365	22300	.	+	0	ID=MGA_1230;product=mevalonate kinase;inference=COORDINATES:ab initio prediction:MetaGeneAnnotator,similar to AA sequence:RefSeq:WP_003640469.1;;locus_tag=LOCUS_12200;gene=mvk;EC_number=2.7.1.36;note=WP_003640469.1 mevalonate kinase (Lactiplantibacillus) [pid:45.0%25%2C q_cov:99.7%25%2C s_cov:99.7%25%2C Eval:8.4e-72],Domain:cl26720:GHMP_kinases_C GHMP kinases C terminal. This model represents mevalonate kinase%2C the third step in the mevalonate pathway of isopentanyl pyrophosphate (IPP) biosynthesis. IPP is a common intermediate for a number of pathways including cholesterol biosynthesis. This model covers enzymes from eukaryotes%2C archaea and bacteria. The related enzyme from the same pathway%2C phosphmevalonate kinase%2C serves as an outgroup for this clade. Paracoccus exhibits two genes within the phosphomevalonate/mevalonate kinase family%2C one of which falls between trusted and noise cutoffs of this model. The degree of divergence is high%2C but if the trees created from this model are correct%2C the proper names of these genes have been swapped. [Central intermediary metabolism%2C Other] [Superfamily%2C Aligned:5-305%2C Eval:2.4e-67%2C score:210.2],MGA_1230
