NZ_CP094655.1-2	MetaGeneAnnotator	CDS	9562	13299	.	+	0	ID=MGA_1354;product=PD-(D/E)XK nuclease family protein;inference=COORDINATES:ab initio prediction:MetaGeneAnnotator,similar to AA sequence:RefSeq:WP_011101883.1;;locus_tag=LOCUS_13380;note=WP_011101883.1 PD-(D/E)XK nuclease family protein (Lactiplantibacillus plantarum) [pid:34.2%25%2C q_cov:98.1%25%2C s_cov:97.4%25%2C Eval:2.7e-164],Domain:cl28251:AddB ATP-dependent helicase/DNAse subunit B [Replication%2C recombination and repair]. DNA repair is accomplished by several different systems in prokaryotes. Recombinational repair of double-stranded DNA breaks involves the RecBCD pathway in some lineages%2C and AddAB (also called RecAB) in other. The AddA protein is conserved between the firmicutes and the alphaproteobacteria%2C while the partner protein is not. The partner may be designated AddB%2C as in Bacillus and in alphaproteobacteria%2C or RexB as in Streptococcus and Lactococcus. Note%2C however%2C that RexB proteins lack an N-terminal GxxGxGK[ST] ATP-binding motif found in Bacillus subtilis and related species%2C and this difference may be important%3B this model represents specifically RexB proteins as found in Streptococcus and Lactococcus. [DNA metabolism%2C DNA replication%2C recombination%2C and repair] [Superfamily%2C Aligned:3-1243%2C Eval:3.9e-132%2C score:430.3],MGA_1354
NZ_CP094655.1-2	MetaGeneAnnotator	CDS	13306	17319	.	+	0	ID=MGA_1355;product=helicase-exonuclease AddAB subunit AddA;inference=COORDINATES:ab initio prediction:MetaGeneAnnotator,similar to AA sequence:RefSeq:WP_011476466.1;;locus_tag=LOCUS_13390;gene=addA;note=WP_011476466.1 helicase-exonuclease AddAB subunit AddA (Ligilactobacillus salivarius) [pid:35.7%25%2C q_cov:97.2%25%2C s_cov:97.8%25%2C Eval:5.0e-209],Domain:cl28312:UvrD Superfamily I DNA or RNA helicase [Replication%2C recombination and repair]. AddAB%2C also called RexAB%2C substitutes for RecBCD in several bacterial lineages. These DNA recombination proteins act before synapse and are particularly important for DNA repair of double-stranded breaks by homologous recombination. The term AddAB is used broadly%2C with AddA homologous between the Firmicutes (as modeled here) and the alphaproteobacteria%2C while the partner AddB proteins show no strong homology across the two groups of species. [DNA metabolism%2C DNA replication%2C recombination%2C and repair] [Superfamily%2C Aligned:8-1316%2C Eval:2.3e-147%2C score:474.3],MGA_1355
