NZ_CP094655.1-84	MetaGeneAnnotator	CDS	6725	7627	.	-	0	ID=MGA_1487;product=L-lactate dehydrogenase;inference=COORDINATES:ab initio prediction:MetaGeneAnnotator,similar to AA sequence:RefSeq:WP_011476460.1;;locus_tag=LOCUS_14650;note=WP_011476460.1 L-lactate dehydrogenase (Ligilactobacillus salivarius) [pid:31.9%25%2C q_cov:99.7%25%2C s_cov:100.0%25%2C Eval:8.6e-34],Domain:cl28073:Ldh_1_C lactate/malate dehydrogenase%2C alpha/beta C-terminal domain. This model represents the NAD-dependent L-lactate dehydrogenases from bacteria and eukaryotes. This enzyme function as as the final step in anaerobic glycolysis. Although lactate dehydrogenases have in some cases been mistaken for malate dehydrogenases due to the similarity of these two substrates and the apparent ease with which evolution can toggle these activities%2C critical residues have been identified which can discriminate between the two activities. At the time of the creation of this model no hits above the trusted cutoff contained critical residues typical of malate dehydrogenases. [Energy metabolism%2C Anaerobic%2C Energy metabolism%2C Glycolysis/gluconeogenesis] [Superfamily%2C Aligned:4-292%2C Eval:2.8e-35%2C score:126.9],MGA_1487
