NZ_CP094655.1-112	MetaGeneAnnotator	CDS	4635	5066	.	-	0	ID=MGA_1647;product=glyoxalase/bleomycin resistance/extradiol dioxygenase family protein;inference=COORDINATES:ab initio prediction:MetaGeneAnnotator,similar to AA sequence:RefSeq:WP_003722084.1;translation=MADIYPYLVFENAKEAMAYYAEQFDADIVARRPLTKAQVDSYGLELTDLDETTAYGEFTIAGQTFICADAMMAMPQTSSLVSIMLDFADDNVAAADFFDHLAASDDQRVTLPFSPQPAGGQAGQIVDRYGITWLISAGFVKHE;locus_tag=LOCUS_16200;note=WP_003722084.1 glyoxalase/bleomycin resistance/extradiol dioxygenase family protein (Listeria monocytogenes) [pid:43.9%25%2C q_cov:94.4%25%2C s_cov:94.6%25%2C Eval:3.3e-26],Domain:cl14632:VOC vicinal oxygen chelate (VOC) family. Toxoflavin lyase (TflA) is metalloenzyme degrading  toxoflavin at the presence of  oxygen%2C Mn(II)%2C and dithiothreitol. TflA is structurally homologous to proteins of the vicinal oxygen chelate superfamily. The structure of TflA contains  fold that displays a rare rearrangement of the structural modules indicative of domain permutation. Moreover%2C unlike the 2-His-1-carboxylate facial triad commonly utilized by vicinal oxygen chelate dioxygenases and other dioxygen-activating non-heme Fe(II) enzymes%2C the metal center in TflA consists of a 1-His-2-carboxylate facial triad. Toxoflavin  is an azapteridine that is toxic to various plants%2C fungi%2C animals%2C and bacteria. [Superfamily%2C Aligned:4-137%2C Eval:4.6e-22%2C score:82.8],MGA_1647
