NZ_CP094655.1-103	MetaGeneAnnotator	CDS	1132	2001	.	-	0	ID=MGA_1681;product=polyphosphate kinase 2 family protein;inference=COORDINATES:ab initio prediction:MetaGeneAnnotator,similar to AA sequence:RefSeq:WP_003642687.1;;locus_tag=LOCUS_16540;note=WP_003642687.1 polyphosphate kinase 2 family protein (Lactiplantibacillus) [pid:56.3%25%2C q_cov:92.0%25%2C s_cov:91.2%25%2C Eval:1.7e-84],Domain:cl11971:PPK2 Polyphosphate kinase 2 (PPK2). Members of this protein family belong to the polyphosphate kinase 2 (PPK2) family%2C which is not related in sequence to PPK1. While PPK1 tends to act in the biosynthesis of polyphosphate%2C or poly(P)%2C members of the PPK2 family tend to use the terminal phosphate of poly(P) to regenerate ATP or GTP from the corresponding nucleoside diphosphate%2C or ADP from AMP as is the case with polyphosphate:AMP phosphotransferase (PAP). Members of this protein family most likely transfer the terminal phosphate between poly(P) and some nucleotide%2C but it is not clear which. [Central intermediary metabolism%2C Phosphorus compounds] [Superfamily%2C Aligned:1-261%2C Eval:3.8e-82%2C score:246.1],MGA_1681
