NZ_CP094655.1-21	MetaGeneAnnotator	CDS	763	1554	.	+	0	ID=MGA_1690;product=hypothetical protein;inference=COORDINATES:ab initio prediction:MetaGeneAnnotator;translation=MKLKQFLLTVCTLIVAVIGFAKVGHAQSVSYQTYKYGTSTTSMADGYYARPATVTVSNGAYVVTMTIRTATNLSAWPVVVNSIDGQAPQNVTKTQSGGYYLYSYSFTTKDLSGVISSSISINVPGVYKANHNISFKFDTSSLPALSGSTSSTSASGANSSSATAAAGVANGSSSSTSGSNDPQLSQKLKKLESQASSQSSAAKAKESRLARSTIAQNDRVQEQSQKNQTLYYFVLVGGILGLLIVIAAAVYFVWSAKKQIPRH;locus_tag=LOCUS_16610;note=TIGR:TIGR03656%3B IsdC: heme uptake protein IsdC [Name:TIGR03656%2C Eval:4.4e-16%2C score:57.3%2C bias:6.6],Domain:cl28250:NEAT Heme-binding NEAT domain [Inorganic ion transport and metabolism]. Isd proteins are iron-regulated surface proteins found in Bacillus%2C Staphylococcus and Listeria species and are responsible for heme scavenging from hemoproteins. The IsdC protein consists of an N-terminal hydrophobic signal sequence%2C a central NEAT (NEAr Transporter%2C pfam05031) domain%2C which confers the ability to bind heme%2C and a C-terminal SrtB processing signal which targets the protein to the cell wall. IsdC is believed to make a direct contact with%2C and transfer heme to%2C the heme-binding component (IsdE) of an ABC transporter in the cytoplasmic membrane%2C and to receive heme from other NEAT-containing heme-binding proteins also localized in the cell wall. [Superfamily%2C Aligned:27-76%2C Eval:8.6e-08%2C score:49.5%2C C-term missing],MGA_1690
