NZ_CP094655.1-122	MetaGeneAnnotator	CDS	1884	3836	.	+	0	ID=MGA_1703;product=glycoside-pentoside-hexuronide (GPH):cation symporter;inference=COORDINATES:ab initio prediction:MetaGeneAnnotator,similar to AA sequence:RefSeq:WP_003643065.1;;locus_tag=LOCUS_16720;note=WP_003643065.1 glycoside-pentoside-hexuronide (GPH):cation symporter (Lactiplantibacillus) [pid:57.6%25%2C q_cov:99.4%25%2C s_cov:98.9%25%2C Eval:8.2e-220],Domain:cl26210:MFS_2 MFS/sugar transport protein. The Glycoside-Pentoside-Hexuronide (GPH):Cation Symporter Family (TC 2.A.2) GPH:cation symporters catalyze uptake of sugars in symport with a monovalent cation (H+ or Na+). Members of this family includes transporters for melibiose%2C lactose%2C raffinose%2C glucuronides%2C pentosides and isoprimeverose. Mutants of two groups of these symporters (the melibiose permeases of enteric bacteria%2C and the lactose permease of Streptococcus thermophilus) have been isolated in which altered cation specificity is observed or in which sugar transport is uncoupled from cation symport (i.e.%2C uniport is catalyzed). The various members of the family can use Na+%2C H+ or Li%2C Na+ or Li+%2C H+ or Li+%2C or only H+ as the symported cation. All of these proteins possess twelve putative transmembrane a-helical spanners. [Transport and binding proteins%2C Carbohydrates%2C organic alcohols%2C and acids] [Superfamily%2C Aligned:7-472%2C Eval:3.0e-59%2C score:203.2],COG:COG2190:NagE Phosphotransferase system IIA component [Category:G%2C Aligned:497-650%2C Eval:3.0e-47%2C score:160.8],MGA_1703
