NZ_CP094655.1-106	MetaGeneAnnotator	CDS	23	247	.	+	0	ID=MGA_1799;product=hypothetical protein;inference=COORDINATES:ab initio prediction:MetaGeneAnnotator;translation=MSCDEPTGALDFETGRAVMQILQDMSRKQGSTVLIVTHNAALAPIADQVIHIHDGRVKEITHQDHPQDIATLEW;locus_tag=LOCUS_17550;note=WP_011837230.1 ABC transporter ATP-binding protein (Streptococcus sanguinis) [pid:72.2%25%2C q_cov:97.3%25%2C s_cov:30.9%25%2C Eval:1.2e-25%2C partial hit],TIGR:TIGR02982%3B heterocyst_DevA: ABC exporter ATP-binding subunit%2C DevA family [Name:TIGR02982%2C Eval:6.6e-16%2C score:56.5%2C bias:0.1],Domain:cl28181:AAA ATPases associated with a variety of cellular activities. Members of this family are ATP-binding cassette (ABC) proteins by homology%2C but belong to energy coupling factor (ECF) transport systems. The architecture in general is two ATPase subunits (or a double-length fusion protein)%2C a T component%2C and a substrate capture (S) component that is highly variable%2C and may be interchangeable in genomes with only one T component. This model identifies many but not examples of the downstream member of the pair of ECF ATPases in Firmicutes and Mollicutes. [Transport and binding proteins%2C Unknown substrate] [Superfamily%2C Aligned:3-60%2C Eval:1.8e-26%2C score:93.3%2C N-term missing],MGA_1799
